Group Project Notice and License

This repository was an iterative individual/group project for CSCI 411
(Database Theory and Design). Per the author, other people contributed to
parts of this codebase, but no commit history was preserved when this
repository was archived, so the exact file-by-file division of authorship
between contributors is not recoverable here (unlike this portfolio's
other group-project repositories, where `git log` made a specific
breakdown possible).

IMPORTANT SCOPE OF THIS LICENSE:

The MIT License below is intended to cover only Daniel Leone's own
contributions to this codebase -- per the author, primarily the
backend/database layer (schema, queries, and the indexing/generation
work; see README.md's Assignment Intent for detail). It is not a
representation that Daniel Leone is the sole author of every file in this
repository. No permission has been obtained from any other contributor to
license or relicense their work, and nothing in this file grants any
right to use, copy, modify, or distribute portions of this Software
authored by someone other than Daniel Leone. Anyone wishing to reuse this
code should treat authorship of any given file as unconfirmed unless
independently verified, and should obtain permission from the actual
author(s) accordingly.

